    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen rebinding things the actions you are binding are often confusing, take for example my movement bindings on colemak-dh:\n```\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'n', 'h' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'e', 'j' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'i', 'k' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'o', 'l' )\n```\nIf you don't move with HJKL, but NEIO, what NEIO is bound to makes no scene. If you are rebinding them the default keybind should not be used to describe what is being bound, as you likely aren't using it.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI think there should be a way to bind to an action and not a key. Helix has a system somewhat like this. My config with a system like this could look like this:\n```\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'n', 'move_cursor_left' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'e', 'move_cursor_down' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'i', 'move_cursor_up' )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'o', 'move_cursor_right' )\n```",
